SETUP INSTRUCTIONS

SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS

Install the following software:

Docker Desktop

Python 3.10 or newer

Node.js 20 or newer

Git

After installing Docker Desktop, RESTART your computer.

CLONE THE PROJECT

Open a terminal and run:

git clone https://github.com/
cd multimedijaProjekt

ELASTICSEARCH + KIBANA (REQUIRED)

This project uses Elasticsearch 7.x (NOT 8 or 9).

Open Docker Desktop

Wait until it says “Docker is running”

From the project root run:

docker-compose up -d

You must see:

es

kibana

If Elasticsearch is not running, the backend WILL NOT WORK.

BACKEND SETUP (FLASK)

Go to backend folder:

cd backend

Create virtual environment:

python -m venv venv

Activate virtual environment (Windows):

venv\Scripts\activate

Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt

Start backend:

python app.py

Backend URL:

http://localhost:5000

NOTES:

There is NO route at /

http://localhost:5000/
 returning 404 is NORMAL

Elasticsearch index is created automatically on first run

AVAILABLE API ENDPOINTS:

GET /api/municipality/<code>

GET /api/municipalities/regions

GET /api/reload (clears and reloads Elasticsearch)

USE THIS TO RELOAD ALL THE DATA IN THE DATABASE

curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/admin/reload-data

FRONTEND SETUP (REACT + VITE)

Go to frontend folder:

cd ../frontend

Install dependencies:

npm install

Start frontend:

npm run dev

Frontend URL:

http://localhost:5173

PROJECT STRUCTURE

multimedijaProjekt/
backend/ Flask API
frontend/ React frontend
docker-compose.yml
SETUP.txt

HOW EVERYTHING CONNECTS

Frontend communicates with backend using HTTP

Backend stores and reads data from Elasticsearch

Elasticsearch acts as the database

Municipality CODE is the shared key between:

SVG map

Backend data

Elasticsearch documents

HOW TO RUN THE PROJECT (EVERY TIME)

Start Docker Desktop

From project root:

docker-compose up -d

Start backend:

cd backend
venv\Scripts\activate
python app.py

Start frontend:

cd frontend
npm run dev

Open browser:

http://localhost:5173